comments.body:
.NET Core has added [X509 support](https://github.com/dotnet/corefx/blob/master/src/System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates/ref/System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.cs).

The affected PowerShell code needs to be reviewed. It may be that enough identical APIs were implemented that we got everything for free... or it may be that PowerShell's use of X509 needs to be completely rewritten.

@daxian-dbw Do you know what's up here?
